(40, 8, 29, 41, 5, 7, 7, 'thou Son of God', 'Connection of Demonic Recognition', 'Both passages emphasize the recognition of Jesus as the Son of God by the demons. They express fear of torment, indicating a shared theme of authority and impending judgment.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 29, 42, 8, 28, 28, 'What have we to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of God?', 'Demons'' Recognition of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the demons'' recognition of Jesus as the Son of God and their fear of torment. They express a similar plea to not be tormented, highlighting their awareness of Jesus'' authority.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 29, 40, 4, 3, 3, 'thou Son of God', 'Connection of Sonship and Temptation', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of Jesus as ''the Son of God.'' In Matthew 8:29, the demons recognize Jesus'' divine sonship, while in Matthew 4:3, the tempter challenges this identity during a moment of vulnerability.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 29, 61, 2, 4, 4, 'torment us before the time', 'Connection of Judgment and Torment', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of judgment and punishment for evil. In Matthew, the demons express fear of torment before the appointed time, while 2 Peter discusses angels being cast down and reserved for judgment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 30, 3, 11, 7, 7, 'an herd of many swine', 'Connection of Swine in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of swine, with Matthew noting their existence and Leviticus declaring them unclean. This connection highlights the cultural and religious significance of swine in biblical texts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 30, 5, 14, 8, 8, 'an herd of many swine', 'Connection of Swine References', 'This connection highlights the presence of swine in both passages. Matthew mentions a herd of swine, while Deuteronomy classifies swine as unclean, emphasizing their significance in dietary laws.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 30, 41, 5, 11, 11, NULL, 'Swine Herd Connection', 'Both passages emphasize a herd of swine feeding, indicating a shared setting in the narrative. This connection highlights the presence of swine in both accounts, suggesting a thematic link between the two.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 30, 23, 65, 3, 4, 'swine', 'Connection of Swine References', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of swine, highlighting its significance in the context of ritual impurity. In Isaiah, the consumption of swine''s flesh is associated with practices that provoke God, while Matthew mentions a herd of swine in a narrative involving demonic possession.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 30, 23, 66, 3, 3, 'an herd of many swine', 'Connection of Swine and Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize the negative view of swine. Matthew mentions a herd of swine, while Isaiah equates swine''s blood with abominable sacrifices.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 30, 42, 8, 32, 32, 'an herd of many swine feeding', 'Swine Herd Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of a herd of swine feeding, linking the two accounts of Jesus'' interaction with demons. This connection highlights the significance of the swine in the narrative.', 'parallel', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 30, 42, 15, 15, 16, 'herd of many swine feeding', 'Feeding of Swine Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of feeding swine, highlighting the significance of swine in the context of the characters'' situations. The mention of swine in Matthew sets a backdrop that resonates with the plight of the character in Luke who is also involved in swine feeding.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 31, 66, 20, 1, 2, 'the devils besought him', 'Connection of Demonic Influence', 'This connection highlights the theme of demonic beings seeking to inhabit and influence the physical world. In Matthew, the devils request to enter the swine, while Revelation depicts the binding of Satan, emphasizing the ultimate authority over demonic forces.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 31, 41, 5, 12, 12, 'suffer us to go away into the herd of swine', 'Request of the Demons', 'Both passages emphasize the demons'' request to enter the swine. The phrasing in each verse shows a direct appeal from the devils to Jesus regarding their desire to inhabit the herd of swine.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 31, 42, 8, 30, 33, 'suffer us to go away into the herd of swine', 'Connection of Demonic Pleas', 'Both passages emphasize the demons'' request to enter the swine. In Matthew, they ask to go into the herd of swine, while in Luke, they specifically request to enter them as well.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 31, 41, 5, 7, 7, NULL, 'Demons'' Plea for Mercy', 'Both passages emphasize the demons'' fear of Jesus and their desire to avoid torment. In Matthew, the demons request to be sent into swine, while in Mark, they plead not to be tormented, highlighting their recognition of Jesus'' authority.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 31, 66, 12, 12, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Demonic Influence', 'This connection highlights the presence of the devil in both passages. In Matthew, the devils seek refuge in swine, while in Revelation, the devil''s wrath is directed at the earth and sea, indicating his ongoing influence and activity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 32, 41, 5, 13, 13, 'the whole herd of swine ran violently down a steep place into the sea', 'Swine and Demons Connection', 'Both passages describe the event where unclean spirits enter a herd of swine, leading to their destruction in the sea. This connection highlights the dramatic outcome of the exorcism performed by Jesus.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 32, 42, 8, 33, 33, 'ran violently down a steep place', 'Swine and Demons Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the expulsion of demons into swine, leading to their destruction in water. The imagery of the herd running violently down a steep place is a direct parallel in both accounts.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 32, 44, 2, 23, 23, 'perished in the waters', 'Destruction and Consequences', 'This connection highlights the theme of destruction resulting from actions taken. In Matthew, the swine perish in the waters, while in Acts, the consequence of crucifying Jesus leads to death.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 32, 44, 4, 28, 28, NULL, 'Divine Control Over Events', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine sovereignty in both passages. In Matthew, the swine''s destruction illustrates God''s authority over creation, while Acts emphasizes that events unfold according to God''s predetermined counsel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 32, 66, 20, 7, 7, 'perished in the waters', 'Connection of Destruction and Release', 'This connection highlights the theme of destruction and chaos associated with both passages. In Matthew, the swine''s violent demise parallels the release of Satan in Revelation, suggesting a return to disorder.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 32, 11, 22, 22, 22, NULL, 'Spiritual Influence and Destruction', 'This connection highlights the theme of destructive influence. In Matthew, the swine''s demise follows a command, while in 1 Kings, a spirit''s persuasion leads to a king''s downfall.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 32, 18, 1, 10, 19, NULL, 'Destruction and Loss', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of destruction and loss, as seen in the swine perishing in water and Job''s possessions and family being taken away. This connection highlights the catastrophic consequences of spiritual conflict and the vulnerability of earthly possessions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 33, 41, 5, 14, 16, 'they that kept them fled', 'Connection of Swine and Possession', 'Both passages emphasize the fleeing of those who tended the swine and their subsequent reporting of the events. This connection highlights the shared narrative of the miraculous healing of the possessed man and the impact on the swine.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 8, 33, 42, 8, 34, 36, 'went their ways into the city, and told', 'Connection of Healing and Reporting', 'Both passages emphasize the reaction of those who witnessed the healing of the possessed man. They fled to tell others about what had happened, highlighting the significance of the event in both accounts.', 'parallel', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
